      "body" : "As far as i understand the network protocol, clients are only informed about the existance of extra blocks in the chain by a 'headers' message, which includes at most 2000 extra blocks. So if you want a counter \"55123/118009 blocks\", i suppose you need to change the network protocol to somehow inform nodes about the length of the current block chain, before downloading all its headers.\n",
